website_summaries.verdict: This toy will truly ignite a kiddo’s imagination as it includes several accessories and rooms in the palace.
pros: Includes 5 different rooms in the palace that coordinate with different Disney princesses
Palace folds closed when not in use and can hold accessories in it
Ideal for ages 3 to 5 years old
cons: Is a bit larger in size, which is something to consider if low on space

customer_reviews.title: Perfect for Disney princess lovers
customer_reviews.text: My daughter wanted a “Barbie” house for Christmas. She’s just not getting into barbies and dolls so I bought this one to see if she’d actually like it. She adores Disney princesses so this was a hit. She loves that there are different areas for different princesses.
customer_reviews.author: chelc

customer_reviews.title: Compact and nice quality
customer_reviews.text: Love this! My 5 year old literally squealed “yay” when she opened this package. I like that this folds into a compact castle for easy storage and I like that it opens up nicely to show different rooms. There’s a kitchen, bathroom, staircase and upstairs area. Not a ton of extras are included, but it does come with a daybed, bathtub and table with cake. It’s a cute house for those who like to play with princesses and barbies.
customer_reviews.author: Marta Gonzales

customer_reviews.title: Flimsy
customer_reviews.text: My 3 year old daughter likes this little playhouse, but it's very flimsy. When we set it up on the carpet it's constantly falling over if she tries to place any of her little princess inside. The cardboard graphics also pop out and are difficult to get back in, and the two outside doors often pop off and have to be reattached. It was fairly inexpensive, but I wouldn't purchase again.
customer_reviews.author: Ashley H

customer_reviews.title: Wonderful house-castle for little princesses 👑

customer_reviews.title: For princess lovers!

customer_reviews.title: Fun but cheeply made

It was on sale when we got it and I'm glad because I do not believe it is worth the original price. It is cheaply made. The cardboard in the walls fall out frequently and things come unattached with minor bumps. You have to unassembled most of the little pieces in order to get the thing to close. It is a tight fit. It is possible for me but my daughter always has trouble trying to fit it all in to close.

product_meta.title: Disney Princess Pop-Up Palace, Castle Playset with Handle and 13 Accessories, 5 Rooms, 2 Feet Tall
product_meta.description: Disney Princess Pop-Up Palace triples as charming playset, useful storage, and carrying case. With the press of a button and the pull of a handle, the Pop-Up Palace expands to 2 levels reaching 2 feet tall! This Disney Princess castle playset is royally arranged when kids are ready to play and easily compactible when parents are ready to pack up the playroom. Open the grand doors of the Pop-Up Palace to reveal 5 different room settings -- Aurora's kitchen, Cinderella's foyer, Ariel's bathroom, Belle's dining room, and a luxurious lounge on the second floor. Fill each room with accessories, like a shell-shaped bathtub, rose-detailed table and chair, royal lounge seat, kitchen stove, and more! Hang the silver-colored chandelier in either the dining room or the lounge. Store accessories inside, close the doors, latch it tight, and carry it with the handle! Princess dolls sold separately. Hasbro and all related terms are trademarks of Hasbro. Copyright Disney
feature_bullets: Kids can store the 13 included accessories in the castle, close the doors, and carry it with them using the handle
Pull the handle to extend second floor of the palace
Open doors to reveal 5 rooms -- Aurora's kitchen, Cinderella's foyer, Ariel's bathroom, Belle's dining room, and luxurious lounge
Kids who loves the vast collection of animated Disney Princess movies will love this Disney Princess castle playset for a birthday gift or holiday present
The castle is inspired by the Disney Princess characters from the animated Disney movies
